WEBVTT

00:00:00.720 --> 00:00:08.480
What is more important, finishing an assignment, or how we go about carrying out the assignment?

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:14.400
Well, our text for today uses the Day of Atonement to illustrate that the way Jesus went about

00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:21.679
living his life was actually even more important than that one act of salvation.

00:00:21.679 --> 00:00:23.280
Now, why?

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:28.320
Well, that's because the way Jesus lived his life carried out his ministry,

00:00:28.480 --> 00:00:30.719
addressed Satan's challenge.

00:00:30.719 --> 00:00:37.200
And Jesus proved that doing things Jehovah's way is the right way to live.

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:45.439
Thus, Jesus by his life upheld Jehovah's sovereignty, and that made his sacrifice acceptable to Jehovah.

00:00:46.399 --> 00:00:52.159
So what are some ways in which Jesus upheld or vindicated Jehovah's sovereignty?

00:00:52.159 --> 00:00:54.880
And how can we imitate Jesus in our assignments?

00:00:55.520 --> 00:00:59.920
Well, there's many things we could talk about today, but let's just consider three ways.

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:06.480
At one, is that Jesus worked on Jehovah's initiatives, not his own.

00:01:07.280 --> 00:01:12.560
Now, as we know, Jesus could calm storms, he could heal people, he could feed people,

00:01:12.560 --> 00:01:18.079
and so Jesus could have decided, well, yes, I'm going to preach, but I'm also going to focus

00:01:18.079 --> 00:01:24.400
my energies on helping people, setting up relief activities, healing of the sick, helping the poor.

00:01:25.359 --> 00:01:28.159
Or the people wanted to make Jesus king.

00:01:28.959 --> 00:01:34.879
He could have decided, well, let me let them make, let me be king, and then I can address some

00:01:34.879 --> 00:01:42.000
of the problems of the day. Or Jesus loved children, and people loved the way Jesus taught.

00:01:42.719 --> 00:01:47.439
So Jesus could have thought, well, I'm going to preach, but I'm going to focus my energy on

00:01:47.439 --> 00:01:52.400
setting up schools so that I can teach young people to learn about Jehovah.

00:01:52.879 --> 00:01:56.079
See, Jesus could have done all of those things, but what did he do?

00:01:56.799 --> 00:02:02.480
Well, let's look at Luke chapter four, in verse 43, and notice what it quotes him saying in

00:02:02.480 --> 00:02:07.840
response to the crowds, wanting him to stay and help them. Luke chapter four, verse 43,

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:14.960
but he said to them, I must also declare the good news of the kingdom of God to other cities,

00:02:14.960 --> 00:02:24.479
because for this I was sent. Jesus never lost sight of why he was there. What his assignment was,

00:02:24.479 --> 00:02:29.439
he stayed focused, and he focused his energies on what Jehovah wanted done.

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:36.479
Well, how can we imitate Jesus in our assignments? Well, as we know, there are many things that we

00:02:36.479 --> 00:02:41.520
could get involved in as an organization. Good things, expanding our relief activities,

00:02:41.520 --> 00:02:47.759
helping the poor, teaching, setting up schools to teach other people, or many other initiatives.

00:02:48.800 --> 00:02:54.639
And there's nothing wrong with us presenting a new idea or initiative to our oversight.

00:02:55.520 --> 00:03:01.919
But what do we do once a decision is made? Well, we follow the direction we throw ourselves into

00:03:01.919 --> 00:03:07.360
the initiatives given to us from our oversight. See, we subject ourselves to what Jehovah wants

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:13.919
his organization to do and how he wants it done. It's not about what we think the organization should

00:03:13.919 --> 00:03:21.840
be doing. It's about what Jehovah wants done. Let's look at another example. Jesus worked within

00:03:21.840 --> 00:03:28.800
the organizational structures that Jehovah had in place or allowed to be in place. Now, Jesus saw

00:03:28.800 --> 00:03:34.639
the hypocrisy, the corruption, the inefficiencies of the Jewish arrangements that were there in place

00:03:34.639 --> 00:03:40.879
at the time. Other arrangements, though not bad, had served their purpose, or were only temporary,

00:03:40.879 --> 00:03:46.960
were soon to end. What would Jesus do? We remember the encounters recorded in Matthew chapter 8,

